Date: 0/0/1985
Source: Woolscours of NZ
Author: BREMNER
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: A description of an unidentified sheepstation in 1881 recorded that a twenty-two man gang ... put through [the sheep-wash] 1250 sheep in a ... day. ... The trough was divided into four partitions with a `crutcher' at each. Four times each sheep was soaped, its back scrubbed with a crutch.
